alluxio.worker.netty

Class DataServerReadHandler

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.netty.channel.ChannelHandlerAdapter
      • io.netty.channel.ChannelInboundHandlerAdapter
        • alluxio.worker.netty.DataServerReadHandler
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    io.netty.channel.ChannelHandler, io.netty.channel.ChannelInboundHandler
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    DataServerBlockReadHandler, DataServerUFSFileReadHandler

    @NotThreadSafe
public abstract class DataServerReadHandler
extends io.netty.channel.ChannelInboundHandlerAdapter
    This class handles Protocol.ReadRequests. Protocol: Check NettyPacketReader for more information. 1. Once a read request is received, the handler creates a PacketReader which reads packets from the block worker and pushes them to the buffer. 2. The PacketReader pauses if there are too many packets in flight, and resumes if there is room available. 3. The channel is closed if there is any exception during the packet read/write.

    • Field Detail

      • mRequest

        protected volatile DataServerReadHandler.ReadRequestInternal mRequest
        This is only updated in the channel event loop thread when a read request starts or cancelled. No need to be locked. When it is accessed outside of the event loop thread, make sure it is not null. For now, all netty channel handlers are executed in the event loop. The packet reader is not executed in the event loop thread.
